BusinessName.BusinessNameLine1Txt: National Association of Energy Service Companies

IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: NAESCOs mission is to promote the delivery of comprehensive energy services including energy efficiency by Energy Service Companies (ESCOS) to maximize customer energy and dollar savings.
IRS990.MissionDesc: NAESCOs mission is to promote the delivery of comprehensive energy services including energy efficiency by Energy Service Companies (ESCOS) to maximize customer energy and dollar savings.
IRS990.Desc: NAESCO conducts an accreditation program that provides users of energy efficiency services confidence in their efficiency service provider. NAESCO advocates and develops policies that encourage energy efficient project implementation and the creation of long-term value for ratepayers and society as a whole.

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: NAESCO provides its membership with special industry information and alerts covering market growth, opportunities and development, as well as produces a periodical newsletter that focuses on industry activity. NAESCO maintains a web site with information about the energy efficiency industry providing information for the public about energy efficiency project implementation and the changing energy efficiency policies and programs conducted by the Federal, State and Local governments.

ProgSrvcAccomActy3Grp.Desc: In 2022, NAESCO hosted several live in person meetings. We held our Federal Workshop in March, our June Members Meeting and our Annual November meeting. We also held 4 live regional meetings. We continue to have robust attendance at our webinars, and typically do two per month. Attendance at live events was very strong in 2022, with about 300 attendees at our largest event.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Members or stockholder classes and rights Part VI line 6
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: NAESCO has dues paying members that have voting rights.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Member election for additional members Part VI line 7a
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: NAESCO members elect the governing body annually.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Governing body decisions Part VI line 7b
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: Decisions of the governing body are generally not subject to member approval.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990 governing body review Part VI line 11
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: The IRS Form 990 is prepared by an independent CPA and is reviewed in detail with the staff. The IRS Form 990 is provided to the Board prior to its filing.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Conflict of interest policy compliance Part VI line 12c
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: The Executive Director monitors financial activity for compliance with the Conflict of Interest Policy.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: CEO executive director top management comp Part VI line 15a
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: The Chair approves the compensation of the Executive Director.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Governing documents etc available to public Part VI line 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: NAESCOs governing documents, conflict of interest policy, and financial statements are generally not available to the public.
